<XMLDocContent PageName="cobalt.graphics.ITexelArray.SourceImageFormat" Title="SourceImageFormat enumeration" xmlns="http://www.cobaltrenderer.com/schema/XMLDocSchema.xsd">
  <Paragraph>
    <PageRef PageName="cobalt.graphics.Welcome">Home</PageRef> ->
    <PageRef PageName="cobalt.graphics.ITexelArray">ITexelArray</PageRef> ->
    SourceImageFormat
  </Paragraph>
  <Section Title="Description">
    <Paragraph>
      The <TypeRef>SourceImageFormat</TypeRef> enumeration describes the component layout of texel array data supplied from CPU memory.
    </Paragraph>
  </Section>
  <Section Title="Members">
    <EnumMemberList>
      <EnumMemberListEntry Name="R">
        Supplies one component conventionally interpreted as red.
      </EnumMemberListEntry>
      <EnumMemberListEntry Name="RG">
        Supplies two components conventionally interpreted as red and green.
      </EnumMemberListEntry>
      <EnumMemberListEntry Name="RGBA">
        Supplies four components conventionally interpreted as red, green, blue, and alpha.
      </EnumMemberListEntry>
      <EnumMemberListEntry Name="X">
        Supplies one generic component where color channel naming is not meaningful.
      </EnumMemberListEntry>
      <EnumMemberListEntry Name="XY">
        Supplies two generic components.
      </EnumMemberListEntry>
      <EnumMemberListEntry Name="XYZW">
        Supplies four generic components.
      </EnumMemberListEntry>
    </EnumMemberList>
  </Section>
  <Section Title="See also">
    <PageRefList>
      <PageRefListEntry PageName="cobalt.graphics.ITexelArray.SetInitialData">ITexelArray.SetInitialData</PageRefListEntry>
